The Central Organization of Trade Unions (Cotu) has hit out at the government for introducing “unreasonable taxes”, saying it should not overburden the people.
In a statement on Friday, Cotu Secretary-General Francis Atwoli noted that Kenyans are suffering the effects of the Covid-19 pandemic, whose first local case was reported in March 2020.



